<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="capabilities.php" src="/private/var/www/paperless/wp-includes/capabilities.php"><scope doc="WordPress User Roles.&#10;&#10;The role option is simple, the structure is organized by role name that store&#10;the name in value of the 'name' key. The capabilities are stored as an array&#10;in the value of the 'capability' key.&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;array (&#10;	'rolename' =&gt; array (&#10;		'name' =&gt; 'rolename',&#10;		'capabilities' =&gt; array()&#10;	)&#10;)&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage User" ilk="class" line="29" lineend="275" name="WP_Roles"><variable citdl="array" doc="List of roles and capabilities.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var array" line="37" name="roles" /><variable citdl="array" doc="List of the role objects.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var array" line="46" name="role_objects" /><variable citdl="array" doc="List of role names.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var array" line="55" name="role_names" /><variable citdl="string" doc="Option name for storing role list.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var string" line="64" name="role_key" /><variable citdl="bool" doc="Whether to use the database for retrieval and storage.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var bool" line="73" name="use_db" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0" ilk="function" line="80" lineend="82" name="__construct" signature="__construct()" /><scope doc="Set up the object properties.&#10;&#10;The role key is set to the current prefix for the $wpdb object with&#10;'user_roles' appended. If the $wp_user_roles global is set, then it will&#10;be used and the role option will not be updated or used.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access protected&#10;@uses $wpdb Used to get the database prefix.&#10;@global array $wp_user_roles Used to set the 'roles' property value." ilk="function" line="96" lineend="115" name="_init" signature="_init()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="111" name="role" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="97" name="wp_user_roles" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="97" name="wpdb" /></scope><scope doc="Reinitialize the object&#10;&#10;Recreates the role objects. This is typically called only by switch_to_blog()&#10;after switching wpdb to a new blog ID.&#10;&#10;@since 3.5.0&#10;@access public" ilk="function" line="126" lineend="145" name="reinit" signature="reinit()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="141" name="role" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="131" name="wp_user_roles" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="131" name="wpdb" /></scope><scope doc="Add role name with capabilities to list.&#10;&#10;Updates the list of roles, if the role doesn't already exist.&#10;&#10;The capabilities are defined in the following format `array( 'read' =&gt; true );`&#10;To explicitly deny a role a capability you set the value for that capability to false.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $role Role name.&#10;@param string $display_name Role display name.&#10;@param array $capabilities List of role capabilities in the above format.&#10;@return WP_Role|null WP_Role object if role is added, null if already exists." ilk="function" line="163" lineend="176" name="add_role" returns="WP_Role" signature="WP_Role add_role(string $role, string $display_name, array $capabilities = array())"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="163" name="role" /><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="163" name="display_name" /><variable citdl="array" default="array()" ilk="argument" line="163" name="capabilities" /></scope><scope doc="Remove role by name.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $role Role name." ilk="function" line="186" lineend="196" name="remove_role" signature="remove_role(string $role)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="186" name="role" /></scope><scope doc="Add capability to role.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $role Role name.&#10;@param string $cap Capability name.&#10;@param bool $grant Optional, default is true. Whether role is capable of performing capability." ilk="function" line="208" lineend="215" name="add_cap" signature="add_cap(string $role, string $cap, bool $grant = true)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="208" name="role" /><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="208" name="cap" /><variable citdl="bool" default="true" ilk="argument" line="208" name="grant" /></scope><scope doc="Remove capability from role.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $role Role name.&#10;@param string $cap Capability name." ilk="function" line="226" lineend="233" name="remove_cap" signature="remove_cap(string $role, string $cap)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="226" name="role" /><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="226" name="cap" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve role object by name.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $role Role name.&#10;@return WP_Role|null WP_Role object if found, null if the role does not exist." ilk="function" line="244" lineend="249" name="get_role" returns="WP_Role" signature="WP_Role get_role(string $role)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="244" name="role" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve list of role names.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@return array List of role names." ilk="function" line="259" lineend="261" name="get_names" returns="array" signature="array get_names()" /><scope doc="Whether role name is currently in the list of available roles.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $role Role name to look up.&#10;@return bool" ilk="function" line="272" lineend="274" name="is_role" returns="bool" signature="bool is_role(string $role)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="272" name="role" /></scope></scope><scope doc="WordPress Role class.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage User" ilk="class" line="284" lineend="385" name="WP_Role"><variable citdl="string" doc="Role name.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var string" line="292" name="name" /><variable citdl="array" doc="List of capabilities the role contains.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var array" line="301" name="capabilities" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor - Set up object properties.&#10;&#10;The list of capabilities, must have the key as the name of the capability&#10;and the value a boolean of whether it is granted to the role.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $role Role name.&#10;@param array $capabilities List of capabilities." ilk="function" line="315" lineend="318" name="__construct" signature="__construct(string $role, array $capabilities)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="315" name="role" /><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="315" name="capabilities" /></scope><scope doc="Assign role a capability.&#10;&#10;@see WP_Roles::add_cap() Method uses implementation for role.&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $cap Capability name.&#10;@param bool $grant Whether role has capability privilege." ilk="function" line="330" lineend="338" name="add_cap" signature="add_cap(string $cap, bool $grant = true)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="330" name="cap" /><variable citdl="bool" default="true" ilk="argument" line="330" name="grant" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="331" name="wp_roles" /></scope><scope doc="Remove capability from role.&#10;&#10;This is a container for {@link WP_Roles::remove_cap()} to remove the&#10;capability from the role. That is to say, that {@link&#10;WP_Roles::remove_cap()} implements the functionality, but it also makes&#10;sense to use this class, because you don't need to enter the role name.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $cap Capability name." ilk="function" line="353" lineend="361" name="remove_cap" signature="remove_cap(string $cap)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="353" name="cap" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="354" name="wp_roles" /></scope><scope doc="Whether role has capability.&#10;&#10;The capabilities is passed through the 'role_has_cap' filter. The first&#10;parameter for the hook is the list of capabilities the class has&#10;assigned. The second parameter is the capability name to look for. The&#10;third and final parameter for the hook is the role name.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $cap Capability name.&#10;@return bool True, if user has capability. False, if doesn't have capability." ilk="function" line="377" lineend="383" name="has_cap" returns="bool" signature="bool has_cap(string $cap)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="377" name="cap" /><variable citdl="apply_filters()" line="378" name="capabilities" /></scope></scope><scope doc="WordPress User class.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage User" ilk="class" line="394" lineend="979" name="WP_User"><variable citdl="array" doc="User data container.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access private&#10;@var array" line="402" name="data" /><variable citdl="int" doc="The user's ID.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var int" line="411" name="ID" /><variable citdl="array" doc="The individual capabilities the user has been given.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var array" line="420" name="caps" /><variable citdl="string" doc="User metadata option name.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var string" line="429" name="cap_key" /><variable citdl="array" doc="The roles the user is part of.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var array" line="438" name="roles" /><variable citdl="array" doc="All capabilities the user has, including individual and role based.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;@var array" line="447" name="allcaps" /><variable citdl="string" doc="The filter context applied to user data fields.&#10;&#10;@since 2.9.0&#10;@access private&#10;@var string" line="456" name="filter" /><variable attributes="private static" citdl="array()" line="458" name="back_compat_keys" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor&#10;&#10;Retrieves the userdata and passes it to {@link WP_User::init()}.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param int|string|stdClass|WP_User $id User's ID, a WP_User object, or a user object from the DB.&#10;@param string $name Optional. User's username&#10;@param int $blog_id Optional Blog ID, defaults to current blog.&#10;@return WP_User" ilk="function" line="473" lineend="506" name="__construct" returns="WP_User" signature="WP_User __construct($id = 0, string $name = '', int $blog_id = '')"><variable default="0" ilk="argument" line="473" name="id" /><variable citdl="string" default="''" ilk="argument" line="473" name="name" /><variable citdl="int" default="''" ilk="argument" line="473" name="blog_id" /><variable line="499" name="data" /><variable citdl="GLOBALS" line="475" name="prefix" /></scope><scope doc="Sets up object properties, including capabilities.&#10;&#10;@param object $data User DB row object&#10;@param int $blog_id Optional. The blog id to initialize for" ilk="function" line="514" lineend="519" name="init" signature="init(object $data, int $blog_id = '')"><variable citdl="object" ilk="argument" line="514" name="data" /><variable citdl="int" default="''" ilk="argument" line="514" name="blog_id" /></scope><scope attributes="static" doc="Return only the main user fields&#10;&#10;@since 3.3.0&#10;&#10;@param string $field The field to query against: 'id', 'slug', 'email' or 'login'&#10;@param string|int $value The field value&#10;@return object Raw user object" ilk="function" line="530" lineend="583" name="get_data_by" returns="object" signature="object get_data_by(string $field, $value)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="530" name="field" /><variable ilk="argument" line="530" name="value" /><variable line="571" name="user" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="531" name="wpdb" /><variable citdl="wp_cache_get()" line="550" name="user_id" /><variable citdl="string" line="551" name="db_field" /></scope><scope doc="Magic method for checking the existence of a certain custom field&#10;&#10;@since 3.3.0" ilk="function" line="590" lineend="603" name="__isset" returns="metadata_exists()" signature="__isset($key)"><variable ilk="argument" line="590" name="key" /></scope><scope doc="Magic method for accessing custom fields&#10;&#10;@since 3.3.0" ilk="function" line="610" lineend="629" name="__get" returns="this.ID" signature="__get($key)"><variable ilk="argument" line="610" name="key" /><variable citdl="this.data" line="617" name="value" /></scope><scope doc="Magic method for setting custom fields&#10;&#10;@since 3.3.0" ilk="function" line="636" lineend="644" name="__set" signature="__set($key, $value)"><variable ilk="argument" line="636" name="key" /><variable ilk="argument" line="636" name="value" /></scope><scope doc="Determine whether the user exists in the database.&#10;&#10;@since 3.4.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@return bool True if user exists in the database, false if not." ilk="function" line="654" lineend="656" name="exists" returns="bool" signature="bool exists()" /><scope doc="Retrieve the value of a property or meta key.&#10;&#10;Retrieves from the users and usermeta table.&#10;&#10;@since 3.3.0&#10;&#10;@param string $key Property" ilk="function" line="667" lineend="669" name="get" returns="this.__get()" signature="get(string $key)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="667" name="key" /></scope><scope doc="Determine whether a property or meta key is set&#10;&#10;Consults the users and usermeta tables.&#10;&#10;@since 3.3.0&#10;&#10;@param string $key Property" ilk="function" line="680" lineend="682" name="has_prop" returns="this.__isset()" signature="has_prop(string $key)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="680" name="key" /></scope><scope doc="Return an array representation.&#10;&#10;@since 3.5.0&#10;&#10;@return array Array representation." ilk="function" line="691" lineend="693" name="to_array" returns="array" signature="array to_array()" /><scope doc="Set up capability object properties.&#10;&#10;Will set the value for the 'cap_key' property to current database table&#10;prefix, followed by 'capabilities'. Will then check to see if the&#10;property matching the 'cap_key' exists and is an array. If so, it will be&#10;used.&#10;&#10;@access protected&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;&#10;@param string $cap_key Optional capability key" ilk="function" line="708" lineend="722" name="_init_caps" signature="_init_caps(string $cap_key = '')"><variable citdl="string" default="''" ilk="argument" line="708" name="cap_key" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="709" name="wpdb" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve all of the role capabilities and merge with individual capabilities.&#10;&#10;All of the capabilities of the roles the user belongs to are merged with&#10;the users individual roles. This also means that the user can be denied&#10;specific roles that their role might have, but the specific user isn't&#10;granted permission to.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@uses $wp_roles&#10;@access public" ilk="function" line="736" lineend="753" name="get_role_caps" signature="get_role_caps()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="748" name="role" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="737" name="wp_roles" /><variable citdl="wp_roles.get_role()" line="749" name="the_role" /></scope><scope doc="Add role to user.&#10;&#10;Updates the user's meta data option with capabilities and roles.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $role Role name." ilk="function" line="765" lineend="770" name="add_role" signature="add_role(string $role)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="765" name="role" /></scope><scope doc="Remove role from user.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $role Role name." ilk="function" line="780" lineend="787" name="remove_role" signature="remove_role(string $role)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="780" name="role" /></scope><scope doc="Set the role of the user.&#10;&#10;This will remove the previous roles of the user and assign the user the&#10;new one. You can set the role to an empty string and it will remove all&#10;of the roles from the user.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $role Role name." ilk="function" line="801" lineend="819" name="set_role" signature="set_role(string $role)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="801" name="role" /><variable citdl="this.roles" line="808" name="old_roles" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="805" name="oldrole" /></scope><scope doc="Choose the maximum level the user has.&#10;&#10;Will compare the level from the $item parameter against the $max&#10;parameter. If the item is incorrect, then just the $max parameter value&#10;will be returned.&#10;&#10;Used to get the max level based on the capabilities the user has. This&#10;is also based on roles, so if the user is assigned the Administrator role&#10;then the capability 'level_10' will exist and the user will get that&#10;value.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param int $max Max level of user.&#10;@param string $item Level capability name.&#10;@return int Max Level." ilk="function" line="840" lineend="847" name="level_reduction" returns="int" signature="int level_reduction(int $max, string $item)"><variable citdl="int" ilk="argument" line="840" name="max" /><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="840" name="item" /><variable citdl="intval()" line="842" name="level" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="841" name="matches" /></scope><scope doc="Update the maximum user level for the user.&#10;&#10;Updates the 'user_level' user metadata (includes prefix that is the&#10;database table prefix) with the maximum user level. Gets the value from&#10;the all of the capabilities that the user has.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public" ilk="function" line="859" lineend="863" name="update_user_level_from_caps" signature="update_user_level_from_caps()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="860" name="wpdb" /></scope><variable citdl="array_reduce()" line="861" name="user_level" /><scope doc="Add capability and grant or deny access to capability.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $cap Capability name.&#10;@param bool $grant Whether to grant capability to user." ilk="function" line="874" lineend="877" name="add_cap" signature="add_cap(string $cap, bool $grant = true)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="874" name="cap" /><variable citdl="bool" default="true" ilk="argument" line="874" name="grant" /></scope><scope doc="Remove capability from user.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $cap Capability name." ilk="function" line="887" lineend="892" name="remove_cap" signature="remove_cap(string $cap)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="887" name="cap" /></scope><scope doc="Remove all of the capabilities of the user.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access public" ilk="function" line="900" lineend="906" name="remove_all_caps" signature="remove_all_caps()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="901" name="wpdb" /></scope><scope doc="Whether user has capability or role name.&#10;&#10;This is useful for looking up whether the user has a specific role&#10;assigned to the user. The second optional parameter can also be used to&#10;check for capabilities against a specific object, such as a post or user.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string|int $cap Capability or role name to search.&#10;@return bool True, if user has capability; false, if user does not have capability." ilk="function" line="921" lineend="947" name="has_cap" returns="bool" signature="bool has_cap($cap)"><variable ilk="argument" line="921" name="cap" /><variable citdl="apply_filters()" line="939" name="capabilities" /><variable citdl="array_slice()" line="927" name="args" /><variable citdl="call_user_func_array()" line="929" name="caps" /></scope><scope doc="Convert numeric level to level capability name.&#10;&#10;Prepends 'level_' to level number.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param int $level Level number, 1 to 10.&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="960" lineend="962" name="translate_level_to_cap" returns="string" signature="string translate_level_to_cap(int $level)"><variable citdl="int" ilk="argument" line="960" name="level" /></scope><scope doc="Set the blog to operate on. Defaults to the current blog.&#10;&#10;@since 3.0.0&#10;&#10;@param int $blog_id Optional Blog ID, defaults to current blog." ilk="function" line="971" lineend="978" name="for_blog" signature="for_blog(int $blog_id = '')"><variable citdl="int" default="''" ilk="argument" line="971" name="blog_id" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="972" name="wpdb" /><variable line="973" name="cap_key" /></scope></scope><scope doc="Map meta capabilities to primitive capabilities.&#10;&#10;This does not actually compare whether the user ID has the actual capability,&#10;just what the capability or capabilities are. Meta capability list value can&#10;be 'delete_user', 'edit_user', 'remove_user', 'promote_user', 'delete_post',&#10;'delete_page', 'edit_post', 'edit_page', 'read_post', or 'read_page'.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;&#10;@param string $cap Capability name.&#10;@param int $user_id User ID.&#10;@return array Actual capabilities for meta capability." ilk="function" line="995" lineend="1270" name="map_meta_cap" returns="array" signature="arr